Susan Cain
Share



Treasurer 
Susan Cain, Ashland, Oregon, joined the faculty of Southern Oregon University as an assistant professor of accounting in 2004. Prior to that position, she was with KPMG Peat Marwick for 21 years in the San Francisco office, where she specialized in banking institutions and was the national partner-in-charge of the Trust Tax Service group. She is currently on the board of Lithia Motors, Inc. (since June 2009), on the advisory board of the Ashland Independent Film Festival and acts as treasurer for a number of nonprofit entities. She graduated with highest honors from Oregon State University with a BA in General Science and received her Master‚Äôs in Taxation in 2005. Susan enjoys theater, reading and participating in activities with her husband and children. 
